0	<text font="9" height="13" left="103" textpieces="0" top="352" width="340">formatting. From the internal space perspective, the major-</text>
 
0	<text font="9" height="13" left="103" textpieces="0" top="369" width="340">ity of the lines contain normal space size while some lines</text>
 
0	<text font="9" height="13" left="103" textpieces="0" top="386" width="340">have large space size, between two adjacent words. We de-</text>
 
0	<text font="9" height="13" left="103" textpieces="0" top="404" width="340">ï¬ne a line as a sparse line if it satisï¬es at least one of the</text>
 
